data.text: #Maryland #COVID #vaccinations. Howard County has reached 90% vaccinated.  But overall, rates are still slow. Hispanics still have a good rate, though. https://t.co/1W38Ek5U8w

#Maryland #COVID by age. I've added per capita plots. On them, deaths are more spread out, highlighting the impact on the elderly.  Seeing a spike in cases in 70s. Too big. Is this an artifact? Rest are declining. Decline in deaths has leveled off. 80s, 60s, and 70s are affected. https://t.co/iGjmJTcNSj

#Maryland #COVID by race.  Cases declining in all.  Per capita, all are equal.  Deaths declining in most, but whites may be ticking up. Per capita they have the most, just above Afr. Americans. https://t.co/wYHoVfvHpK
#Maryland #COVID  #hospitalizations continue their decline for both beds and ICU at rates that are slightly increasing. https://t.co/A3QRdJABl5

#Maryland #COVID by zip, case totals.These numbers are much lower than last week, making me think the spike was some sort of data artifact. But the zips in Baltimore are still higher than they were. Baltimore takes the top 4 spots, then Cumberland is which back to where it was. https://t.co/zTsDER8mDi
#Maryland #COVID by zip, per capita.  Worst zips are Kitzmiller (4.19 new cases/1000) in Garrett and Rawlings (3.69) in Allegany. Both are much lower than last week. https://t.co/14aAuDkBFD

#Maryland #COVID deaths by county.  Per capita, the hardest hit are Allegany, Washington, and Talbot at fairly low levels: 0.06 deaths/1000. Together, the 3 make of 13.5 % of the deaths in Maryland.  Howard County is high on the list per capita, but Baltimore still has the most. https://t.co/gJUTNbsqwi

#Maryland #COVID by county. Cases continue steadily downward in most counties. the uptick in Garrett is seen in the zoom. It also looks like PG is seeing an uptick. Deaths are going down in most of the top 5, but have leveled in Montgomery. Seeing a uptick in outlying. Artifact? https://t.co/NsAY9YSmNo
